{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0fe6d381-a14d-4877-9112-ef84f803913a","content":"Here's the correct attribute for each framework:\n\n| Framework | Attribute |\n|-----------|-----------|\n| **MSTest** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **xUnit** | `[Fact(Skip = \"reason\")]` or `[Theory(Skip = \"reason\")]` |\n| **NUnit** | `[Ignore(\"reason\")]` |\n| **TUnit** | `[Skip(\"reason\")]` |\n\n**Example usage:**\n\n```csharp\n// MSTest\n[TestMethod]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyMsTest() { }\n\n// xUnit\n[Fact(Skip = \"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyXunitTest() { }\n\n// NUnit\n[Test]\n[Ignore(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyNunitTest() { }\n\n// TUnit\n[Test]\n[Skip(\"Waiting on bug fix #1234\")]\npublic void MyTunitTest() { }\n```\n\nNote: xUnit is the only one where skip is a property on the test attribute itself rather than a separate attribute.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9121f293-8f2f-4a9e-b597-625858765020","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about test-skipping attributes across four .NET test frameworks. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":309,"requestId":"702D:1A47AE:1D630:23620:69F2AC8C"},"id":"6b559194-d962-47ba-8284-c9c8dfb37d39","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:12:53.959Z","parentId":"464b19eb-e132-447d-8cb6-184688c949f2"}
